The paper also focuses on random graph models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses power law degree distributions, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
